@startuml
title Payment lifecycle — server-enforced state machine (PaymentStatus)

skinparam BackgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam state {
  BackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  BorderColor #1168bd
  ArrowColor #555
}

[*] --> Outstanding : CreatePaymentHandler\n(landlord — RequireLandlord;\nrent due, no submission yet)

Outstanding --> Pending : SubmitPaymentHandler\n(tenant — RequireTenant;\nReceiptUpload or ManualRequest)
Rejected --> Pending : SubmitPaymentHandler\n(tenant resubmits;\nclears RejectedAt + RejectionReason)

Pending --> Confirmed : ConfirmPaymentHandler\n(landlord — RequireLandlord)
Pending --> Rejected : RejectPaymentHandler\n(landlord; sets RejectionReason)

Confirmed --> [*] : terminal

note right of Pending
  The Payment entity is **anemic** — every guard lives in the
  Application-layer command handler, never on the entity.
  Illegal transitions return **409 ConflictException**:
   - Submit  requires Outstanding **or** Rejected
   - Confirm requires Pending
   - Reject  requires Pending
  Each successful transition publishes an integration event
  (payment.created / submitted / confirmed / rejected) — see events.puml.
end note

note bottom of Rejected
  **Rejected is NOT terminal** (rejection "Model 1"): the tenant can
  resubmit, looping back to Pending. **Confirmed** is the only terminal
  business state. (Model 2 — Rejected becomes terminal with a superseding
  Outstanding row — is a documented follow-up.)
end note

@enduml
